	)
	(text_box "CAN OVER RJ45 HYBRID TOPOLOGY SUMMARY\nThis layout supports both Daisy-Chain (Device-to-Device) and Hub-and-Spoke (Hanging) configurations using standard off-the-shelf T568B Ethernet cables. It uses true twisted pairs for signal integrity.\n\nAPPROACH:\n\nTwo RJ45 Jacks (Jack A and Jack B) are placed on each board.\n\nIn Daisy-Chain Mode: Cable goes from Jack B of Node N to Jack A of Node N+1. Onboard termination switch is ON only at the first and last physical devices.\n\nIn Hanging Hub Mode: A single cable runs from the Hub to Jack A of the device. Jack B remains empty. The CAN signal travels down to the transceiver on Pins 4 and 5, jumps across the PCB to Pins 7 and 8, and travels back up the same cable to the Hub. Loopback bridging is handled inside the Hub. Onboard termination switches are OFF; termination is placed inside the Hub.\n\nJACK A PINOUT (MAIN INLET / HANGING PORT)\nPin 1: V+ Power (Bus pass-through)\nPin 2: GND Ground (Bus pass-through)\nPin 3: Unused\nPin 4: CAN_H In (Connects to Transceiver CAN_H and Jack B Pin 7)\nPin 5: CAN_L In (Connects to Transceiver CAN_L and Jack B Pin 8)\nPin 6: Unused\nPin 7: CAN_H Return Loop (Connects ONLY to Jack B Pin 4)\nPin 8: CAN_L Return Loop (Connects ONLY to Jack B Pin 5)\n\nJACK B PINOUT (DAISY-CHAIN OUTLET)\nPin 1: V+ Power (Bus pass-through)\nPin 2: GND Ground (Bus pass-through)\nPin 3: Unused\nPin 4: CAN_H Out (Connects ONLY to Jack A Pin 7)\nPin 5: CAN_L Out (Connects ONLY to Jack A Pin 8)\nPin 6: Unused\nPin 7: From Transceiver CAN_H / Jack A Pin 4\nPin 8: From Transceiver CAN_L / Jack A Pin 5"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 218.44 63.5 0)
		(size 88.9 78.7399)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
		(stroke
			(width 0)
			(type solid)
		)
		(fill
			(type none)
		)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "d4f59ca7-67f0-43b5-bdc4-dcfddecd9640")
	)
	(text_box "Q's\n\n- Where to get 3V3_A from?\n- Where to tie D and A GND?\n\nJust like the power side, HPVSS should share a clean ground path with the chip's internal analog ground (AVSS), keeping it isolated from the high-current switching ground of the Class-D speaker (SPKVSS) until they meet at a single \"star ground\" point on the board."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 165.1 127 0)
		(size 48.26 33.02)
		(margins 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525 0.9525)
